MoneyMap v0.9.3-alpha UI/UX rescue pass
Focus
This pass responds to the visible issues found during quick testing across mobile and desktop.
Changes
Replaced wireframe-style navigation symbols with friendlier emoji icons.
Rebuilt the mobile bottom nav into a calmer five-item rail.
Cleaned up the More sheet icon treatment.
Reworked budget cards so they no longer appear as raw gray blocks.
Added stronger desktop and mobile budget card styles for Home and Budgets.
Tightened mobile spacing across headers, cards, metric tiles, and actions.
Fixed row select controls that were stretching into oversized table pills.
Added responsive card behavior for account, debt, and holding tables on mobile.
Added investment holding cards and better investment insights.
Reworked the investment allocation chart labels to reduce overlap and clipping.
Hid obstructive chart tooltips on phone widths.
Standardized the visible build label and backup metadata to v0.9.3-alpha.
